# Forms & Validation

Use `react-hook-form` for form state and `valibot` for schema validation. No exceptions.

## Schema Definition

Validation schemas live alongside their service types in `services/<domain>/`:

```typescript
// services/auth/auth.types.ts
import * as v from 'valibot'

export const LoginSchema = v.object({
  email: v.pipe(v.string(), v.email()),
  password: v.pipe(v.string(), v.minLength(8)),
})

export type LoginFormData = v.InferOutput<typeof LoginSchema>

export interface LoginResponse {
  token: string
  user: UserResponse
}
```

## Form Hook Pattern

```tsx
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form'
import { valibotResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/valibot'
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next'
import { FormControl, TextInput } from '@primer/react'
import type { LoginFormData } from '@/services/auth'
import { LoginSchema } from '@/services/auth'

export const LoginForm = ({ onSubmit }: LoginFormProps) => {
  const { t: tAuth } = useTranslation('auth')
  const { register, handleSubmit, formState: { errors } } = useForm<LoginFormData>({
    resolver: valibotResolver(LoginSchema),
  })

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
      <FormControl>
        <FormControl.Label>{tAuth('email')}</FormControl.Label>
        <TextInput {...register('email')} />
        {errors.email && (
          <FormControl.Validation variant="error">
            {tAuth(`validation.${errors.email.message}`)}
          </FormControl.Validation>
        )}
      </FormControl>
    </form>
  )
}
```

## Rules

- NEVER use `useState` for form fields — always `react-hook-form`
- NEVER validate manually — always via valibot schema + resolver
- Schemas are the single source of truth for form types (`v.InferOutput`)
- Schemas and their types live in `services/` — never in components
- Form components receive `onSubmit` via props (DI) — never handle submission internally
- Visible labels use `useTranslation` — never hardcoded strings (see i18n rule)
